#: pcbnew/dialogs/panel_setup_rules_help_2constraints.h:2
msgid ""
"### Constraints\n"
"\n"
"| Constraint type           | Argument "
"type                                                                                                         "
"| "
"Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             "
"|\n"
"|---------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `annular_width`           | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Checks the width of annular rings on vias."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          "
"|\n"
"| `assertion`               | \"&lt;"
"expression>\"                                                                                                     "
"| Checks the given expression."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `bridged_mask`            "
"|                                                                                                                       "
"| Checks for solder mask bridges between copper items.  This constraint does "
"not take a min/opt/max value.  In combination with a severity clause, this "
"constraint can be used to allow or disallow solder mask bridging in various "
"conditions."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                       "
"|\n"
"| `clearance`               | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Specifies the **electrical** clearance between copper objects of different "
"nets.  (See `physical_clearance` if you wish to specify clearance between "
"objects regardless of net.)<br><br>To allow copper objects to overlap "
"(collide), create a `clearance` constraint with the `min` value less than "
"zero (for example, `-1`)."
"<br>                                                                                                                      "
"|\n"
"| `courtyard_clearance`     | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Checks the clearance between footprint courtyards and generates an error "
"if any two courtyards are closer than the `min` distance.  If a footprint "
"does not have a courtyard shape, no errors will be generated from this "
"constraint."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                               "
"|\n"
"| `creepage`                | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Specifies the creepage distance between copper objects of different nets."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `diff_pair_gap`           | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Checks the gap between coupled tracks in a differential pair.  Coupled "
"tracks are segments that are parallel to each other.  Differential pair gap "
"is not tested on uncoupled portions of a differential pair (for example, the "
"fanout from a component)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `diff_pair_uncoupled`     | "
"max                                                                                                                   "
"| Checks the distance that a differential pair track is routed uncoupled "
"from the other polarity track in the pair (for example, where the pair fans "
"out from a component, or becomes uncoupled to pass around another object "
"such as a via)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                         "
"|\n"
"| `disallow`                | "
"`track`<br>`via`<br>`through_via`<br>`blind_via`<br>`buried_via`<br>`micro_via`<br>`pad`<br>`zone`<br>`text`<br>`graphic`<br>`hole`<br>`footprint`<br> "
"| Specify one or more object types to disallow, separated by spaces.  For "
"example, `(constraint disallow track)` or `(constraint disallow track via "
"pad)`.  If an object of this type matches the rule condition, a DRC error "
"will be created.<br><br>This constraint is essentially the same as a keepout "
"rule area, but can be used to create more specific keepout restrictions."
"<br>                                                                   |\n"
"| `edge_clearance`          | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Checks the clearance between objects and the board edge.<br><br>This can "
"also be thought of as the \"milling tolerance\" as the board edge will "
"include all graphical items on the `Edge.Cuts` layer as well as any *oval* "
"pad holes.  (See `physical_hole_clearance` for the drilling "
"tolerance.)<br>                                                                                                                                                    "
"|\n"
"| `length`                  | min/"
"max                                                                                                               "
"| Checks the total routed length for the nets that match the rule condition "
"and generates an error for each net that is below the `min` value (if "
"specified) or above the `max` value (if specified) of the constraint."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                               "
"|\n"
"| `hole`                    | min/"
"max                                                                                                               "
"| Checks the size (diameter) of a drilled hole in a pad or via.  For oval "
"holes, the smaller (minor) diameter will be tested against the `min` value "
"(if specified) and the larger (major) diameter will be tested against the "
"`max` value (if specified)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                            "
"|\n"
"| `hole_clearance`          | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Checks the clearance between a drilled hole in a pad or via and copper "
"objects on a different net.  The clearance is measured from the diameter of "
"the hole, not its center."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `hole_to_hole`            | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Checks the clearance between mechanically-drilled holes in pads and vias.  "
"The clearance is measured between the diameters of the holes, not between "
"their centers.<br><br>This constraint is soley for the protection of drill "
"bits.  The clearance between **laser-drilled** (microvias) and other non-"
"mechanically-drilled holes is not checked, nor is the clearance between "
"**milled** (oval-shaped) and other non-mechanically-drilled holes.<br> |\n"
"| `physical_clearance`      | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Checks the clearance between two objects on a given layer (including non-"
"copper layers).<br><br>While this can perform more general-purpose checks "
"than `clearance`, it is much slower.  Use `clearance` where possible."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                            "
"|\n"
"| `physical_hole_clearance` | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Checks the clearance between a drilled hole in a pad or via and another "
"object, regardless of net. The clearance is measured from the diameter of "
"the hole, not its center.<br><br>This can also be thought of as the "
"\"drilling tolerance\" as it only includes **round** holes (see "
"`edge_clearance` for the milling tolerance)."
"<br>                                                                                                                    "
"|\n"
"| `silk_clearance`          | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Checks the clearance between objects on silkscreen layers and other "
"objects."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `skew`                    | "
"max                                                                                                                   "
"| Checks the total skew for the nets that match the rule condition, that is, "
"the difference between the length of each net and the average of all the "
"lengths of each net that is matched by the rule.  If the absolute value of "
"the difference between that average and the length of any one net is above "
"the constraint `max` value, an error will be generated."
"<br>                                                                                   "
"|\n"
"| `solder_mask_expansion`   | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Specifies the solder mask expansion for pads, shapes and "
"tracks.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `solder_paste_abs_margin` | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Specifies the absolute solder paste clearance for pads.  Usually negative "
"to inset the paste.<br><br>The final solder paste clearance will be the "
"absolute clearance plus the relative "
"clearance.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `solder_paste_rel_margin` | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Specifies the relative solder paste clearance for pads.  Usually negative "
"to inset the paste.<br><br>The final solder paste clearance will be the "
"absolute clearance plus the relative "
"clearance.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `thermal_relief_gap`      | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Specifies the width of the gap between a pad and a zone with a thermal-"
"relief connection."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `thermal_spoke_width`     | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Specifies the width of the spokes connecting a pad to a zone with a "
"thermal-relief connection."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      "
"|\n"
"| `track_width`             | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Checks the width of track and arc segments.  An error will be generated "
"for each segment that has a width below the `min` value (if specified) or "
"above the `max` value (if specified)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             "
"|\n"
"| `track_angle`             | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Checks the angle between two connected track segments.  An error will be "
"generated for each connected pair with an angle below the `min` value (if "
"specified) or above the `max` value (if specified)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "
"|\n"
"| `track_segment_length`    | min/"
"max                                                                                                               "
"| Checks the length of track and arc segments.  An error will be generated "
"for each segment that has a length below the `min` value (if specified) or "
"above the `max` value (if specified)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `via_count`               | "
"max                                                                                                                   "
"| Counts the number of vias on every net matched by the rule condition.  If "
"that number exceeds the constraint `max` value on any matched net, an error "
"will be generated for that net."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               "
"|\n"
"| `via_dangling`            "
"|                                                                                                                       "
"| Checks for vias that are unconnected or connected on only one layer.  This "
"constraint does not take a min/opt/max value.  In combination with a "
"severity clause, this constraint can be used to allow or disallow dangling "
"vias in various conditions."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                              "
"|\n"
"| `zone_connection`         | "
"`solid`<br>`thermal_reliefs`<br>`none`                                                                                "
"| Specifies the connection to be made between a zone and a pad."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       "
"|\n"
"\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"### Kendala\n"
"\n"
"| Tipe kendala           | Tipe "
"argumen                                                                                                         "
"| "
"Deskripsi                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             "
"|\n"
"|---------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `annular_width`           | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Memeriksa lebar cincin annular pada via."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          "
"|\n"
"| `assertion`               | \"&lt;"
"ekspresi>\"                                                                                                     "
"| Memeriksa ekspresi yang diberikan."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `bridged_mask`            "
"|                                                                                                                       "
"| Memeriksa jembatan masker solder antara item tembaga. Kendala ini tidak "
"mengambil nilai min/opt/max. Dikombinasikan dengan klausa severity, kendala "
"ini dapat digunakan untuk mengizinkan atau melarang penjembatan masker "
"solder dalam berbagai kondisi."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                       "
"|\n"
"| `clearance`               | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Menentukan jarak bebas **elektrik** antara objek tembaga dari net berbeda. "
"(Lihat `physical_clearance` jika ingin menentukan jarak bebas antara objek "
"terlepas dari net.)<br><br>Untuk mengizinkan objek tembaga tumpang tindih, "
"buat kendala `clearance` dengan nilai `min` kurang dari nol (misalnya, `-1`)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                      "
"|\n"
"| `courtyard_clearance`     | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Memeriksa jarak bebas antara courtyard footprint dan menghasilkan "
"kesalahan jika ada dua courtyard yang lebih dekat dari jarak `min`. Jika "
"footprint tidak memiliki bentuk courtyard, tidak ada kesalahan yang "
"dihasilkan dari kendala ini."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                               "
"|\n"
"| `creepage`                | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Menentukan jarak creepage antara objek tembaga dari net berbeda."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `diff_pair_gap`           | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Memeriksa celah antara trek yang digandeng dalam pasangan diferensial. "
"Trek yang digandeng adalah segmen yang sejajar satu sama lain. Celah "
"pasangan diferensial tidak diuji pada bagian yang tidak digandeng (misalnya, "
"fanout dari komponen)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `diff_pair_uncoupled`     | "
"max                                                                                                                   "
"| Memeriksa jarak trek pasangan diferensial yang diroute tanpa gandeng dari "
"trek polaritas lain dalam pasangan (misalnya, di mana pasangan melakukan "
"fanout dari komponen, atau tidak digandeng untuk melewati objek lain seperti "
"via)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                         "
"|\n"
"| `disallow`                | "
"`track`<br>`via`<br>`through_via`<br>`blind_via`<br>`buried_via`<br>`micro_via`<br>`pad`<br>`zone`<br>`text`<br>`graphic`<br>`hole`<br>`footprint`<br> "
"| Tentukan satu atau lebih tipe objek yang tidak diizinkan, dipisahkan "
"dengan spasi. Misalnya, `(constraint disallow track)` atau `(constraint "
"disallow track via pad)`. Jika objek dari tipe ini cocok dengan kondisi "
"aturan, kesalahan DRC akan dibuat.<br><br>Kendala ini pada dasarnya sama "
"dengan area aturan keepout, tetapi dapat digunakan untuk membuat pembatasan "
"keepout yang lebih spesifik."
"<br>                                                                   |\n"
"| `edge_clearance`          | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Memeriksa jarak bebas antara objek dan tepi papan.<br><br>Ini juga dapat "
"dianggap sebagai \"toleransi milling\" karena tepi papan akan mencakup semua "
"item grafis di lapisan `Edge.Cuts` serta lubang pad *oval*. (Lihat "
"`physical_hole_clearance` untuk toleransi "
"pengeboran.)<br>                                                                                                                                                    "
"|\n"
"| `length`                  | min/"
"max                                                                                                               "
"| Memeriksa total panjang routed untuk net yang cocok dengan kondisi aturan "
"dan menghasilkan kesalahan untuk setiap net yang berada di bawah nilai `min` "
"(jika ditentukan) atau di atas nilai `max` (jika ditentukan) dari kendala."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                               "
"|\n"
"| `hole`                    | min/"
"max                                                                                                               "
"| Memeriksa ukuran (diameter) lubang bor pada pad atau via. Untuk lubang "
"oval, diameter yang lebih kecil (minor) akan diuji terhadap nilai `min` "
"(jika ditentukan) dan diameter yang lebih besar (major) akan diuji terhadap "
"nilai `max` (jika ditentukan)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                            "
"|\n"
"| `hole_clearance`          | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Memeriksa jarak bebas antara lubang bor pada pad atau via dan objek "
"tembaga pada net berbeda. Jarak bebas diukur dari diameter lubang, bukan "
"pusatnya."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `hole_to_hole`            | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Memeriksa jarak bebas antara lubang yang dibor secara mekanis pada pad dan "
"via. Jarak bebas diukur antara diameter lubang, bukan antara pusatnya."
"<br><br>Kendala ini semata-mata untuk perlindungan mata bor. Jarak bebas "
"antara lubang yang **dibor laser** (microvia) dan lubang yang tidak dibor "
"secara mekanis lainnya tidak diperiksa, begitu pula jarak bebas antara "
"lubang yang **dimilling** (berbentuk oval) dan lubang yang tidak dibor "
"secara mekanis lainnya.<br> |\n"
"| `physical_clearance`      | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Memeriksa jarak bebas antara dua objek pada lapisan tertentu (termasuk "
"lapisan non-tembaga).<br><br>Meskipun ini dapat melakukan pemeriksaan lebih "
"umum dari `clearance`, namun jauh lebih lambat. Gunakan `clearance` jika "
"memungkinkan."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                            "
"|\n"
"| `physical_hole_clearance` | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Memeriksa jarak bebas antara lubang bor pada pad atau via dan objek lain, "
"terlepas dari net. Jarak bebas diukur dari diameter lubang, bukan pusatnya."
"<br><br>Ini juga dapat dianggap sebagai \"toleransi pengeboran\" karena "
"hanya mencakup lubang **bulat** (lihat `edge_clearance` untuk toleransi "
"milling)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                    "
"|\n"
"| `silk_clearance`          | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Memeriksa jarak bebas antara objek pada lapisan sablon dan objek lainnya."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 "
"|\n"
"| `skew`                    | "
"max                                                                                                                   "
"| Memeriksa total skew untuk net yang cocok dengan kondisi aturan, yaitu "
"perbedaan antara panjang setiap net dan rata-rata semua panjang setiap net "
"yang cocok dengan aturan. Jika nilai absolut perbedaan antara rata-rata "
"tersebut dan panjang net mana pun berada di atas nilai `max` kendala, "
"kesalahan akan dihasilkan."
"<br>                                                                                                                                   "
"|\n"
"| `solder_mask_expansion`   | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Menentukan ekspansi masker solder untuk pad, bentuk, dan "
"trek.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `solder_paste_abs_margin` | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Menentukan jarak bebas pasta solder absolut untuk pad. Biasanya negatif "
"untuk memperkecil pasta.<br><br>Jarak bebas pasta solder akhir adalah jarak "
"bebas absolut ditambah jarak bebas "
"relatif.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `solder_paste_rel_margin` | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Menentukan jarak bebas pasta solder relatif untuk pad. Biasanya negatif "
"untuk memperkecil pasta.<br><br>Jarak bebas pasta solder akhir adalah jarak "
"bebas absolut ditambah jarak bebas "
"relatif.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        "
"|\n"
"| `thermal_relief_gap`      | "
"min                                                                                                                   "
"| Menentukan lebar celah antara pad dan zona dengan koneksi thermal-relief."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `thermal_spoke_width`     | "
"opt                                                                                                                   "
"| Menentukan lebar jeruji yang menghubungkan pad ke zona dengan koneksi "
"thermal-relief."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      "
"|\n"
"| `track_width`             | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Memeriksa lebar segmen trek dan busur. Kesalahan akan dihasilkan untuk "
"setiap segmen yang memiliki lebar di bawah nilai `min` (jika ditentukan) "
"atau di atas nilai `max` (jika ditentukan)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             "
"|\n"
"| `track_angle`             | min/opt/"
"max                                                                                                           "
"| Memeriksa sudut antara dua segmen trek yang terhubung. Kesalahan akan "
"dihasilkan untuk setiap pasangan yang terhubung dengan sudut di bawah nilai "
"`min` (jika ditentukan) atau di atas nilai `max` (jika ditentukan)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "
"|\n"
"| `track_segment_length`    | min/"
"max                                                                                                               "
"| Memeriksa panjang segmen trek dan busur. Kesalahan akan dihasilkan untuk "
"setiap segmen yang memiliki panjang di bawah nilai `min` (jika ditentukan) "
"atau di atas nilai `max` (jika ditentukan)."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           "
"|\n"
"| `via_count`               | "
"max                                                                                                                   "
"| Menghitung jumlah via pada setiap net yang cocok dengan kondisi aturan. "
"Jika jumlah tersebut melebihi nilai `max` kendala pada net mana pun yang "
"cocok, kesalahan akan dihasilkan untuk net tersebut."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               "
"|\n"
"| `via_dangling`            "
"|                                                                                                                       "
"| Memeriksa via yang tidak terhubung atau terhubung hanya pada satu lapisan. "
"Kendala ini tidak mengambil nilai min/opt/max. Dikombinasikan dengan klausa "
"severity, kendala ini dapat digunakan untuk mengizinkan atau melarang via "
"menggantung dalam berbagai kondisi."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                              "
"|\n"
"| `zone_connection`         | "
"`solid`<br>`thermal_reliefs`<br>`none`                                                                                "
"| Menentukan koneksi yang dibuat antara zona dan pad."
"<br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       "
"|\n"
"\n"
"\n"

#: pcbnew/dialogs/panel_setup_rules_help_3items.h:2
msgid ""
"### Items\n"
"\n"
" * `A` &nbsp;&nbsp; _the first (or only) item under test_\n"
" * `B` &nbsp;&nbsp; _the second item under test (for binary tests)_\n"
" * `L` &nbsp;&nbsp; _the layer currently under test_\n"
"\n"
"<br>\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"### Item\n"
"\n"
" * `A` &nbsp;&nbsp; _item pertama (atau satu-satunya) yang diuji_\n"
" * `B` &nbsp;&nbsp; _item kedua yang diuji (untuk uji biner)_\n"
" * `L` &nbsp;&nbsp; _lapisan yang sedang diuji_\n"
"\n"
"<br>\n"
"\n"

#: pcbnew/dialogs/panel_setup_rules_help_4severity_names.h:2
